{
  "texts": [
    "This high perplexity indicates that the sequence of words is inconsistent with the patterns observed in typical language use.",
    "To identify nonsensical concepts, we first compute the perplexity of the original nonsensical statement S, denoted as P P L original.",
    "Perplexity is determined by calculating the exponential of the negative average of the log probabilities of each word in the sentence.",
    "Specifically, it is computed as:P P L original = exp - 1 N N i=1 log P(w i | S)(1)where P(w i | S) is the probability assigned to word w i given the surrounding context within the input statement S. A higher P P L original suggests that the sentence as a whole deviates significantly from what the language model perceives as a typical, commonsensical sentence.",
    "Next, to pinpoint the specific token responsible for this deviation, we systematically mask each word in the sentence and compute the perplexity of the masked sentences."
  ]
}